sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"active_lock_reason":null,"body":"I find myself commonly writing the trivial utility function `normalize(x) = x/norm(x)` for geometric computing.  Julia has the useful utility `cross()` in linalg - maybe `normalize()` and `normalize!()` belong there too?  I see that ImmutableArrays.jl has defined `unit()` for this though that name clashes with a different use in SIUnits.

For greater than 1D arrays, `normalize(x, dim)` acting along a dimension would be a useful generalization for me personally.  A p-norm version might also be useful.

@simondanisch - this is very relevant to 3D graphics - maybe you have some thoughts?
