/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-08-02T04:34:11Z","updated_at":"2024-08-02T04:34:11Z","author_association":"MEMBER","body":"I've put in a targeted ambiguity warning. As explained in the commit message, I've made two very specific forms

    function (@f(x))
        body
    end

    function ($f)
        body
    end

into an ambiguity error. I think these are the only truly ambiguous cases as the parser doesn't know how the interpolated syntax will expand. It could be either of these:

        function (@f(x),)
            body
        end

        function @f(x)
            body
        end

